<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="generic diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Generic diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Afrotropical species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Mesembrius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesembrius" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesembrius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. (i.e. excluding representatives of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Mesembrius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesembrius (Vadonimyia)" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Vadonimyia">Mesembrius Vadonimyia</taxonomicName>
, cf. Introduction) have the following combination of diagnostic characters: postpronotum pilose; compound eye bare (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 46–51" captionStartId="F24" captionText="Figures 46 - 51. Mesembrius spp., head, frontal view 46 M. arcuatus sp. nov. (♂) 47 M. caffer (Loew) (nominal morph) (♂) 48 M. caffer (Loew) (spined morph) (♂) 49 M. ctenifer Hull syn. nov. (♂) 50 M. capensis (Macquart) (♂) 51 M. chapini Curran (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures46-51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557485" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">46</figureCitation>
- 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 79–82" captionStartId="F30" captionText="Figures 79 - 82. Mesembrius spp., head, frontal view 79 M. simplicipes Curran (♂) 80 M. sulcus sp. nov. (♀) 81 M. tarsatus (Bigot) (♀) 82 M. vockerothi sp. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures79-82" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557491" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">82</figureCitation>
); wing vein R4+5 strongly sinuate; wing vein M1 processive distally (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 127–130" captionStartId="F39" captionText="Figures 127 - 130. Mesembrius spp., right wing 127 M. arcuatus sp. nov. (♂) 128 M. caffer (Loew) (nominal morph) (♂) 129 M. capensis (Macquart) (♂) 130 M. chapini Curran (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures127-130" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557500" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">127</figureCitation>
- 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 147–150" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figures 147 - 150. Mesembrius spp., right wing 147 M. sulcus sp. nov. (♂) 148 M. tarsatus (Bigot) (♂) 149 M. tibialis sp. nov. (♂) 150 M. vockerothi sp. nov. (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures147-150" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557505" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">150</figureCitation>
); wing cell r1 open (rarely, cell r1 is narrowly open as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 139–142" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figures 139 - 142. Mesembrius spp., right wing 139 M. nigriceps Curran (♂) 140 M. perforatus (Speiser) (♂) 141 M. platytarsis Curran syn. nov. (♂) 142 M. regulus (Hull) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures139-142" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557503" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">142</figureCitation>
); thorax with katepimeron conspicuously pilose; and metabasitarsus with basoventral globuliferous setae (e.g. Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 185–188" captionStartId="F53" captionText="Figures 185 - 188. Mesembrius spp., mesoleg, dorsal view 185 M. perforatus (Speiser) (♀). Metaleg, posterior view 186 M. chapini Curran (♂) 187 M. sulcus sp. nov. (♂). Metaleg, ventral view 188 M. tibialis sp. nov. (♂). Abbreviations: bt-basitarsus, fem-femur, tib-tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures185-188" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557513" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">185</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 193–196" captionStartId="F55" captionText="Figures 193 - 196. Mesembrius spp., metaleg, dorsal view 193 M. platytarsis Curran syn. nov. (♂) 194 M. simplicipes Curran (♂). Metaleg, anterior view 195 M. caffer (Loew) (nominal morph) (♂) 196 M. caffer (Loew) (spined morph) (♂). Abbreviations: bt-basitarsus, fem-femur, tib-tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1046.57052.figures193-196" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/557515" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">196</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
